race.description: Harry O'leary Breaking In & Pretraining Hcp (56)
race.comment: PURE RAIN (12) made a strong late bid only to just miss when first-up last start over 1115m at Kyneton. Will strip a lot fitter this time around and looks hard to beat in this suitable race, despite the dreadful gate. HOT CHILLI MAMA (7) finished fifth two runs back then improved last start but found a couple better over 1535m at Geelong, beaten 3.5 lengths after being in contention on the turn. Well placed and there is no reason she cannot find winning ways. SNICK (9) isn't exactly what you'd call a trustworthy conveyance but her best form is more than good enough for a race of this quality and she'll be better for the first-up outing. LITTLE SUNSET (13) ran an improved race at big odds last start and draws to get the chance to go on with it. EPICUS (4) has been racing consistently and the stable wouldn't be making the trip from Moe if there wasn't something particularly appealing about this race.
